-- Tata Power Plans to Invest $1 Billion in Wind Power Plants, PTI Reports
-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-11-21T05:28:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-21/tata-power-plans-to-invest-1-billion-in-wind-power-plants-pti-reports.html
Tata Power Ltd. plans to invest
about 50 billion rupees ($1.1 billion) in wind energy, the Press
Trust of India reported, citing Banmali Agrawala, executive
director of strategy and business development.   The power producer aims to have at least 25 percent of its
generation capacity, or about 8,000 megawatts, fueled by clean
sources including wind, solar, hydro, geothermal and gas by
2017, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
